{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"A plugin whose manifest is missing a required field is rejected before any code from that plugin is executed.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is between manifest validation and module-loading orchestration, not a single function. Test must verify the loader reads manifest, rejects invalid plugin, and never imports its entry module (e.g., side-effect file/counter stays untouched). Rejected Unit because behavior explicitly includes cross-module sequencing: `rejected before any code ... executed`. Rejected System/Agentic/Workflow because behavior text has no subprocess/network/OS-only primitive, no AI/ML call, and no multi-agentic chain.","test_description":"Create a temp plugin directory with one plugin missing a required manifest field and an entry module that writes a sentinel on import. Run loader end-to-end in-process; assert validation error is reported and sentinel was not written.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.22,"Integration":0.74,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"When plugin A declares a dependency on plugin B, plugin B's `onLoad` hook is called before plugin A's.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Real failure appears in wiring between dependency resolver and hook executor. A pure unit test of topological sort can miss mistakes in applying resolved order to actual hook invocation. Rejected Unit because behavior requires observing real `onLoad` call sequence across plugins. Rejected System/Agentic/Workflow: no real external infra, no model output, no multi-agentic pipeline in behavior text.","test_description":"Build two test plugins on disk: A depends on B; each `onLoad` appends its name to a shared log. Run loader and assert log order is `[B, A]`.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.08,"Integration":0.86,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"When two plugins each declare a dependency on the other, the loader reports the cycle and loads neither.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Need resolver + load gate integration: detect cycle and ensure neither plugin lifecycle runs. Unit graph-cycle detection alone would miss regression where loader still imports or executes hooks after detection. Rejected Unit due to required handoff from detection to execution suppression (`loads neither`). Rejected System/Agentic/Workflow because no subprocess/network/OS-only dependency, no AI/ML output dependency, no multi-agentic sequence.","test_description":"Create plugins A and B with mutual dependencies; each entry/hook writes a sentinel if run. Execute loader; assert cycle error is reported and no sentinel indicates import/hook execution for either plugin.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.12,"Integration":0.82,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"A plugin's `onLoad` hook is only invoked after the plugin's entry module has been imported and executed.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Ordering failure is at module boundary between module import side effects and lifecycle invocation. Must run real loader path that imports module then calls exported hook. Rejected Unit because single-function tests cannot prove import-time execution happened before hook call in real wiring. Rejected System/Agentic/Workflow: behavior does not require subprocess/real network/OS primitive, no AI/ML dependency, no multi-agentic chain.","test_description":"Make a plugin whose entry module sets `globalThis.pluginInitFlag = true` on import and whose `onLoad` asserts that flag is true (or records observed state). Run loader and assert `onLoad` saw the post-import state.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.84,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When a plugin throws an error during its `onLoad` hook, the loader continues initializing the remaining plugins that do not depend on it.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is orchestration/state-propagation across dependency graph + error handling: one failing hook should not block unrelated plugins, while dependency constraints are respected. Unit tests of exception handling or graph logic alone can miss this interaction. Rejected Unit because behavior explicitly spans multiple plugins and dependency relationships. Rejected System/Agentic/Workflow: no subprocess/network/OS-only primitive, no AI/ML output dependence, no multi-agentic staged decisions.","test_description":"Create plugins: X throws in `onLoad`, Y independent, Z depends on X. Run loader; assert X failure is recorded, Y `onLoad` ran, and Z did not initialize due to dependency on failed X.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.07,"Integration":0.87,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}}]}
